-- Leighton’s Thiess Unit Wins $182 Million Sydney Water Contract
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-01-25T17:42:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-25/leighton-s-thiess-unit-wins-182-million-sydney-water-contract.html
Leighton Holdings Ltd. (LEI) ’s Thiess unit
has been awarded a five-year operations and maintenance contract
with Sydney Water, Australia’s largest water utility, that’s
worth A$175 million ($182 million).  Thiess said today in a statement to the Australian
Securities Exchange that the contract “was one of the largest
of its kind in Australia’s water industry.” Thiess’s clients
also include the Wonthaggi reverse-osmosis desalination plant on
the Bass coast near  Melbourne .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
